{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RVcKHv6Bz6rg6oiTomnw5H","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the codebase at `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode`. Here's my detailed findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. BRIDGE_MODE Contract Content\n\n**File**: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/bridge-mode-contract.md`\n\nBridge mode (Remote Control / CCR) is defined as a production-grade Rust contract for remote session management with the following key characteristics:\n\n**Objective**: Define clearer boundaries between remote session creation, lifecycle management, and archive operations while preserving current behavior.\n\n**Key Components**:\n- **Entitlement/gate logic**: Controls access to bridge mode\n- **Session lifecycle API**: Create, fetch, archive, resume operations\n- **Session ID compatibility**: `session_` prefix (local) ↔ `cse_` prefix (transport) translation\n- **Archive semantics**: Idempotent operations where HTTP 409 is treated as success-equivalent\n- **State transitions**: Terminal states (Archived, Expired, Failed) cannot transition back to Running\n\n**Primary Contracts**:\n- `RemoteSessionService` trait with 5 async methods\n- `CcrClient` trait (HTTP transport layer)\n- Typed error hierarchies: `RemoteSessionError` and `CcrClientError`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Bridge-Mode Related Files\n\nAll files are organized by crate:\n\n**Specification & Governance**:\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/bridge-mode-contract.md`\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/bootstrap/tests/spec_governance_gate.rs`\n\n**Application Layer (Policy/Service)**:\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/spec_contracts.rs`\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/remote_session_service.rs`\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/application/src/remote_session_service_tests.rs`\n\n**Remote Runtime (HTTP Transport)**:\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/remote-runtime/src/contracts.rs`\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/remote-runtime/src/ccr_client.rs`\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/remote-runtime/src/ccr_client_tests.rs`\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/remote-runtime/src/contracts_tests.rs`\n\n**Platform Layer (Composition)**:\n- `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/remote_trigger_dispatch_service.rs` (similar pattern for trigger dispatch)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Platform Crate Structure\n\n**Location**: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/`\n\n**Files**:\n```\nlib.rs                                    (234 bytes - module declarations)\nsecurity.rs                               (5.0 KB)\nsecurity_tests.rs                         (3.6 KB)\nremote_trigger_dispatch_service.rs        (2.1 KB)\nremote_trigger_dispatch_service_tests.rs  (6.8 KB)\ntrigger_scheduler_service.rs              (4.1 KB)\ntrigger_scheduler_service_tests.rs        (8.6 KB)\n```\n\n**Dependencies** (in Cargo.toml):\n- `ccode-application` (workspace)\n- `ccode-remote-runtime` (workspace)\n- `ccode-cron` (local)\n- `ccode-state-store` (local)\n- `async-trait`, `serde_json`, `thiserror`, `regex`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Security Implementation\n\n**Location**: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/platform/src/security.rs`\n\n**Key Components**:\n\n1. **`SecretScanner` trait**: Scans content for secret patterns\n   - Method: `scan(&self, content: &str) -> Vec<SecretFinding>`\n\n2. **`DefaultSecretScanner` implementation**: Detects 4 secret patterns\n   - OpenAI API keys (`sk-*` or `sk-proj-*`)\n   - GitHub PATs (`ghp_*`)\n   - AWS access key IDs (`AKIA*`)\n   - Private key blocks (`-----BEGIN...PRIVATE KEY-----`)\n\n3. **`ScanThenWritePolicy<S>`**: Policy enforcement trait\n   - `validate_then_scan()`: Validates path canonicalization before scanning content\n   - `scan_remote_payload()`: Scans payload without file I/O\n\n4. **Path Validation**:\n   - `validate_canonical_path()`: Prevents parent directory traversal (`..`)\n   - `canonicalize_with_missing_segments()`: Handles non-existent paths\n   - Prevents symlink escape attacks (Unix-specific test)\n\n**Error Types**:\n- `PathValidationError`: 5 variants (ParentTraversalDenied, RootNotFound, OutsideRoot, InvalidTargetPath, Io)\n- `PolicyError`: Wraps PathValidationError or SecretDetected with findings\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Patterns in the Codebase\n\n**Remote Session Service Tests** (`remote_session_service_tests.rs`):\n- **Mock pattern**: `MockCcrClient` with `VecDeque<Result<T>>` for queued responses\n- **Async tests**: Uses `#[tokio::test]` for async functions\n- **Error mapping**: Tests error translation from `CcrClientError` → `RemoteSessionError`\n- **Policy enforcement**: Tests `policy_enabled` flag short-circuits\n- **Timeout handling**: `archive_on_shutdown_best_effort()` degradation tests\n\n**CCR Client Tests** (`ccr_client_tests.rs`):\n- **Unit tests**: Standalone functions for compatibility and error classification\n- **Prefix translation**: Roundtrip tests for `session_` ↔ `cse_` prefixes\n- **Error masking**: Verifies internal body/trace details are stripped\n- **Status classification**: 401→Unauthorized, 403→Forbidden, 5xx→Http\n\n**Contracts Tests** (`contracts_tests.rs`):\n- **State machine validation**: Tests all allowed/forbidden transitions\n- **Terminal state enforcement**: Archived/Expired/Failed cannot transition out\n- **Full transition matrix**: Comprehensive combinatorial testing\n- **Type-safe error mapping**: `transition_to()` returns `Result<State, Error>`\n\n**Security Tests** (`security_tests.rs`):\n- **Traversal attacks**: Rejects `../` patterns\n- **Boundary checks**: Ensures paths resolve within root\n- **Symlink escape**: Unix-specific test for symlink-based traversal\n- **Secret detection**: Tests pattern matching with audit labels\n- **Call ordering**: Verifies validate-then-scan order before writes\n\n---\n\n## 6. Workspace Structure (Cargo.toml)\n\n**Location**: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/Cargo.toml`\n\n**Members** (14 crates):\n```\ndomain, ports, config, application, provider, mcp-runtime, \nremote-runtime, platform, session, tools, cron, state-store, \nbootstrap, cli\n```\n\n**Key Internal Paths**:\n- `ccode-domain` → `crates/domain`\n- `ccode-application` → `crates/application` (policy layer)\n- `ccode-remote-runtime` → `crates/remote-runtime` (HTTP transport)\n- `ccode-platform` → `crates/platform` (composition/services)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Types & Functions for Bridge Mode\n\n### Core Types\n\n**RemoteSessionState** (enum):\n- `Pending`, `Running`, `Idle`, `RequiresAction` (non-terminal)\n- `Archived`, `Expired`, `Failed` (terminal)\n- Methods: `can_transition_to(target)`, `transition_to(target) -> Result`\n\n**RemoteSessionSummary** (struct):\n- `session_id: String` (opaque, prefix-agnostic)\n- `title: Option<String>`\n- `environment_id: Option<String>`\n- `state: RemoteSessionState`\n\n**ArchivePolicy** (struct):\n- `timeout: Duration`\n- `idempotent: bool`\n\n**ArchiveResult** (enum):\n- `Archived` (normal success)\n- `AlreadyArchived` (409 conflict, treated as success)\n\n### Service Methods\n\n**RemoteSessionService** trait:\n1. `create_session(req) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, RemoteSessionError>`\n2. `fetch_session(session_id) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, RemoteSessionError>`\n3. `archive_session(session_id, policy) -> Result<(), RemoteSessionError>`\n4. `update_title(session_id, title) -> Result<(), RemoteSessionError>`\n5. `reconcile_resume(session_id) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, RemoteSessionError>`\n\n**CcrClient** trait:\n1. `create(req) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, CcrClientError>`\n2. `get(session_id) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, CcrClientError>`\n3. `archive(session_id) -> Result<ArchiveResult, CcrClientError>`\n4. `patch_title(session_id, title) -> Result<(), CcrClientError>`\n\n### HTTP Transport Implementation\n\n**HttpCcrClient** (`ccr_client.rs`):\n- Session ID translation: `session_abc` ↔ `cse_abc` (endpoints only)\n- Retry logic: Exponential backoff with configurable max_retries\n- Status classification: 401→Unauthorized, 403→Forbidden, 409→AlreadyArchived\n- Auth headers: Bearer token + `x-org-id` header\n\n### Error Mapping\n\n**CcrClientError** → **RemoteSessionError**:\n```\nUnauthorized        → AuthUnavailable\nForbidden          → EntitlementDenied\nHttp(\"status 404\") → NotFound\nTimeout            → Upstream(\"timeout\")\nInvalidPayload     → Upstream(\"invalid response payload\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Governance & Testing Requirements\n\n**Spec Governance Gate** (`spec_governance_gate.rs`):\n\nFor BRIDGE_MODE contract, the codebase enforces:\n\n✓ **Spec Content Checklist**:\n- At least 6 code evidence anchors\n- Explicit crate boundary/ownership section\n- Constants classification\n- Error taxonomy section\n- Contract + integration test matrix\n- CLI behavior tests or security tests\n\n✓ **Code Anchor Checklist**:\n- Trait names: `RemoteSessionService`, `CcrClient`\n- Error types: `RemoteSessionError`, `CcrClientError`\n- Allowed trait crates: `crates/application/`, `crates/remote-runtime/`\n\n✓ **Cross-Spec Consistency**:\n- Terminal state semantics defined\n- Idempotent/cleanup/orphan behavior documented\n- Fail-closed policy wording required\n\n---\n\n## 9. Architectural Layering\n\n**Flow**: `cli → application → remote-runtime → platform`\n\n1. **`crates/application`**: Policy decisions, error translation, state validation\n   - Owns: `RemoteSessionService` trait\n   - Depends on: `CcrClient` from remote-runtime\n   - Never decides: fail-open/fail-close (that's policy's job)\n\n2. **`crates/remote-runtime`**: HTTP transport, auth headers, compatibility\